193
00:18:33,061 --> 00:18:34,460
How do you do, Miss Shelby?

194
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:36,998
Miss Shelby's been waiting to see you.

195
00:18:37,065 --> 00:18:38,430
Won't you come in?

196
00:18:41,403 --> 00:18:44,497
- What seems to be the trouble?
- It's my shoulder, doctor.

197
00:18:44,573 --> 00:18:46,302
It aches a little.

198
00:18:56,218 --> 00:18:58,379
<i>I thought Lloyd Craig</i>
<i>would be easy,</i>

199
00:18:58,453 --> 00:19:00,887
<i>but only part of him reached out to me.</i>

200
00:19:00,956 --> 00:19:02,583
<i>The other part clung desperately</i>

201
00:19:02,658 --> 00:19:05,786
<i>to the ideals that</i>
<i>have driven him all his life.</i>

202
00:19:05,861 --> 00:19:09,729
<i>Ideals that have sent him into the slums</i>
<i>to heal the poor.</i>

203
00:19:09,798 --> 00:19:13,859
<i>Ideals so strong they've become</i>
<i>a shield against his poverty,</i>

204
00:19:13,936 --> 00:19:16,063
<i>his bitter Ioneliness.</i>

205
00:19:16,138 --> 00:19:18,299
<i>I had to smash that shield.</i>

206
00:19:18,373 --> 00:19:22,002
<i>I had to. I had to. I had to.</i>

207
00:19:36,892 --> 00:19:38,120
Darling?

208
00:19:39,194 --> 00:19:42,425
What's the matter? You look so unhappy.

209
00:19:42,497 --> 00:19:45,295
Oh, that. Don't think about it now.

210
00:19:45,367 --> 00:19:48,359
I can't think of anything else.
Day and night I...

211
00:19:48,437 --> 00:19:49,699
Give me a cigarette.

212
00:19:50,839 --> 00:19:52,033
Please.

213
00:20:06,889 --> 00:20:09,119
Look, Margot. No, don't interrupt me.

214
00:20:09,191 --> 00:20:11,125
I've got to talk about it now.

215
00:20:14,529 --> 00:20:17,828
- I can't go through with it.
- You don't have to, dear.

216
00:20:17,900 --> 00:20:20,698
- But I thought you said...
- I've been thinking about it, too.

217
00:20:20,769 --> 00:20:23,897
I can't stand watching you
fight yourself this way.

218
00:20:23,972 --> 00:20:25,371
I don't want to hurt you.

219
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:28,000
I don't want to do anything
that's going to make you unhappy.

220
00:20:28,076 --> 00:20:29,668
And us?

221
00:20:29,745 --> 00:20:32,646
- What about us?
- What can there be about us?

222
00:20:32,714 --> 00:20:34,045
What do you mean?

223
00:20:34,116 --> 00:20:37,142
- What about all our plans?
- Our plans?

224
00:20:37,219 --> 00:20:39,483
Why do you think
I want you to save Frankie?

225
00:20:39,554 --> 00:20:41,681
Do you think
I'd care whether he's alive or dead?

226
00:20:41,757 --> 00:20:44,555
Not a bit. It meant money for us.

227
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:47,458
It meant being together, you and I.

228
00:20:47,529 --> 00:20:50,589
- That's what I cared about.
- We can still be married.

229
00:20:50,666 --> 00:20:52,566
I have my practice, I have my prison work.

230
00:20:52,634 --> 00:20:55,762
- We can start together and...
- No, I couldn't, Lloyd.

231
00:20:55,837 --> 00:20:58,567
- I just couldn't.
- You said you loved me.

232
00:21:00,042 --> 00:21:02,806
Do you remember the first time
I came to see you in your office?

233
00:21:02,878 --> 00:21:06,041
Your dingy, gloomy office
in that dingy, dirty street,

234
00:21:06,114 --> 00:21:08,014
