369
00:33:07,635 --> 00:33:09,000
All right, Pete.

370
00:33:09,370 --> 00:33:10,860
Okay, open them up.

371
00:34:00,822 --> 00:34:02,084
- Everything okay?
- Perfect.

372
00:34:02,156 --> 00:34:04,420
They're gonna put him in the oven.
I've got the orders in my pocket.

373
00:34:04,492 --> 00:34:06,357
Good. Get moving, quick.

374
00:34:25,012 --> 00:34:26,843
- Here's your dough.
- Yeah, thank you.

375
00:34:31,919 --> 00:34:33,819
Thanks, Mr. Vincent.

376
00:34:33,888 --> 00:34:36,186
- Now beat it and keep your mouth shut.
- Hey, wait a minute!

377
00:34:36,257 --> 00:34:38,487
Where's the body
you was gonna switch for Olins?

378
00:34:38,559 --> 00:34:40,720
- Shut up, you.
- No, where is it? You promised me.

379
00:34:40,795 --> 00:34:45,232
I gotta deliver a body to the crematorium.
I'll be in a spot, Mr. Vincent.

380
00:34:52,373 --> 00:34:53,772
There's his body.

381
00:34:56,110 --> 00:34:57,099
Let's go.

382
00:35:28,576 --> 00:35:29,975
Come on, let's go.

383
00:35:53,034 --> 00:35:55,002
All right, put him over there.

384
00:35:56,838 --> 00:35:59,705
- Did you lock the door?
- Yes. Don't worry about it.

385
00:36:01,909 --> 00:36:03,240
Okay.

386
00:36:05,079 --> 00:36:06,546
Here's yours.

387
00:36:10,785 --> 00:36:12,912
It's worth more.

388
00:36:16,257 --> 00:36:19,693
Well, I guess Pete won't be needing this.

389
00:36:20,595 --> 00:36:22,358
Here's another five. Split it.

390
00:36:22,430 --> 00:36:23,988
Okay, Vince.

391
00:36:24,365 --> 00:36:25,730
Now, get out.

392
00:36:31,539 --> 00:36:32,528
Well?

393
00:36:34,008 --> 00:36:35,908
Sure, sure, we're going.

394
00:36:56,697 --> 00:36:59,962
- Anything I can do to help, Doc?
- Yes, be quiet.

395
00:38:17,912 --> 00:38:19,345
Strap that ankle.

396
00:40:04,852 --> 00:40:06,149
Reflex hammer.

397
00:40:22,903 --> 00:40:24,200
Lloyd, you've done it!

398
00:40:24,271 --> 00:40:26,671
- You've saved him! Oh, darling!
- Keep quiet.

399
00:40:29,210 --> 00:40:31,508
There's blankets in the closet.

400
00:40:54,635 --> 00:40:56,159
He's coming to.

401
00:43:24,985 --> 00:43:26,452
I'm alive.

402
00:43:27,221 --> 00:43:28,688
I'm alive!

403
00:43:31,725 --> 00:43:34,751
Margot, baby.

404
00:43:35,896 --> 00:43:38,490
- Wait in the other room, Doc.
- What for?

405
00:43:38,565 --> 00:43:41,056
I wanna talk to Frankie. Go on outside.

406
00:43:41,135 --> 00:43:43,933
- He's in no condition to talk now.
- Get out.

407
00:43:44,004 --> 00:43:46,302
Please, just for a few minutes.

408
00:44:01,822 --> 00:44:03,790
It's all right now, Frankie boy.

409
00:44:03,857 --> 00:44:05,950
Everything's all right now.

410
00:44:06,660 --> 00:44:08,594
Yeah, it's all right now, isn't it?

411
00:44:08,662 --> 00:44:11,563
I'm alive, Margot. Alive.

412
00:44:13,434 --> 00:44:15,800
Everything's okay now.

413
00:44:24,978 --> 00:44:26,707
Cigarette, Frankie?

414
00:44:28,048 --> 00:44:29,743
Oh, yeah. Thanks.

415
00:44:53,374 --> 00:44:56,275
You've been a good boy, Jim.
I won't forget it.

416
00:45:07,221 --> 00:45:09,485
Everything else I want to forget.

417
00:45:12,960 --> 00:45:15,451
We'll go someplace, someplace far away.

418
00:45:15,529 --> 00:45:17,997
I got dough, plenty of it.
And we'll go now, right now.

419
00:45:18,065 --> 00:45:20,590
- Jim, get me a car and some...
- Snap out of it, Frankie.

420
00:45:20,667 --> 00:45:22,760
- Snap out of what?
- Do you think I'm crazy?

421
00:45:22,836 --> 00:45:26,397
There are 5,000 cops in this state
who know your face as well as their own.

422
00:45:26,473 --> 00:45:28,441
- She's right, Frankie.
- Who asked you?

423
00:45:28,509 --> 00:45:30,534
Stop it, Frankie. You know it's true.

424
00:45:30,611 --> 00:45:33,546
- We'd be picked up in an hour.
- Maybe.

425
00:45:36,517 --> 00:45:37,609
What's on your mind?

426
00:45:37,684 --> 00:45:41,120
Simply this, you've got to get a new
face, a face nobody'll ever recognize.

427
00:45:41,188 --> 00:45:42,985
- Yeah, but...
- Wait a minute. It's all set.

428
00:45:43,056 --> 00:45:44,921
We've got a plastic surgeon
who's gonna do the job.

429
00:45:44,992 --> 00:45:46,619
It'll take about three weeks.

430
00:45:46,693 --> 00:45:49,389
You can stay here meanwhile,
but we've got to work fast.

431
00:45:49,463 --> 00:45:51,294
What are we waiting for? Get him.

432
00:45:51,365 --> 00:45:55,529
- It'll cost $25,000, Frankie.
- So what?

433
00:45:55,602 --> 00:45:58,298
It'll have to come out of that money
you've got put away.

434
00:45:58,372 --> 00:46:02,502
Nothing comes out of that money,
until I take it out myself.

435
00:46:03,977 --> 00:46:05,774
Vince'll pay for the doctor.

436
00:46:05,846 --> 00:46:08,406
I'm into you for sixty Gs already.

437
00:46:08,482 --> 00:46:11,076
60,000? For what?

438
00:46:11,151 --> 00:46:14,518
Do you want an itemized account
of what it cost to save your life?

439
00:46:17,324 --> 00:46:18,757
Lay out the dough, Vince.

440
00:46:18,826 --> 00:46:21,260
You know you'll get it back
as soon as I can get out of here.

441
00:46:22,262 --> 00:46:23,786
No soap, Frankie.

442
00:46:23,864 --> 00:46:25,695
You've just been gassed.

443
00:46:25,766 --> 00:46:27,927
How do I know
what kind of shape you're in?

444
00:46:28,001 --> 00:46:31,266
Maybe you wouldn't be able
to pull through an operation.

445
00:46:31,338 --> 00:46:34,000
What are you trying to say, Jimmy boy?

446
00:46:34,074 --> 00:46:36,440
I got 60 grand coming to me now.

447
00:46:36,510 --> 00:46:38,876
I can't afford to take a chance.

448
00:46:38,946 --> 00:46:41,141
You better dig up that dough.

449
00:46:43,083 --> 00:46:45,643
You think I'm going to die, too, huh?

450
00:46:45,719 --> 00:46:48,654
No, darling. No, of course not.

451
00:46:48,722 --> 00:46:53,159
It's just that if... If Vince is right,
if something did happen to you,

452
00:46:53,227 --> 00:46:55,821
what would become of me?
What would I do?

453
00:46:55,896 --> 00:46:58,262
You've got to think about me, too.

454
00:46:59,066 --> 00:47:01,626
Why don't you tell me
where the money is?

455
00:47:01,735 --> 00:47:03,498
Don't you trust me, darling?

456
00:47:03,570 --> 00:47:06,505
Yeah, sure I trust you. Sure.

457
00:47:07,474 --> 00:47:09,203
Hey, maybe you're right.

458
00:47:09,877 --> 00:47:12,368
Maybe you have gotta be protected.

459
00:47:13,547 --> 00:47:16,641
Both of you.
In case anything happens to me.

460
00:47:18,452 --> 00:47:20,511
Yeah, maybe you're right.

461
00:47:23,190 --> 00:47:24,817
I'll make a deal.

462
00:47:25,425 --> 00:47:28,189
You lay out the dough for the new face,

463
00:47:28,262 --> 00:47:32,494
