00:52:02,769 --> 00:52:03,963
Yes.

493
00:52:07,774 --> 00:52:11,005
Well, I guess that takes care of that angle.

494
00:52:11,077 --> 00:52:12,669
Sorry to bother you at this hour, Doc,

495
00:52:12,746 --> 00:52:15,510
but there's been somebody
playing pranks with Frankie's body

496
00:52:15,582 --> 00:52:17,812
and I had to make sure he was dead.

497
00:52:17,884 --> 00:52:19,181
Pranks?

498
00:52:19,252 --> 00:52:20,344
Yeah.

499
00:52:21,254 --> 00:52:23,085
Some hoodlums hijacked
the morgue truck,

500
00:52:23,156 --> 00:52:26,455
knocked off the driver,
and walked away with Frankie.

501
00:52:28,061 --> 00:52:30,029
Well, I gotta get going.

502
00:52:31,832 --> 00:52:36,064
Oh, by the way, Doc,
got a stay-awake pill handy?

503
00:52:36,136 --> 00:52:38,036
- Stay-awake pill?
- Yeah.

504
00:52:38,805 --> 00:52:41,171
My office hours are worse than yours.

505
00:52:42,209 --> 00:52:45,235
I still got a couple of house calls to make.

506
00:52:50,784 --> 00:52:51,978
Thanks.

507
00:52:53,653 --> 00:52:56,918
Guess you doctors
don't get much sleep either?

508
00:52:58,325 --> 00:53:00,259
Doctors and coppers.

509
00:53:00,327 --> 00:53:04,093
A lot of coppers chasing shadows
in the streets tonight.

510
00:53:04,164 --> 00:53:07,099
- You mean Olins' body?
- No.

511
00:53:07,167 --> 00:53:08,964
The guys who took it.

512
00:53:09,803 --> 00:53:12,499
I'm going out after a lad named Vincent.

513
00:53:13,874 --> 00:53:17,002
I've been a long time
saving it up for that guy.

514
00:53:17,911 --> 00:53:21,779
When I get him,
I'm going to lean on him heavy.

515
00:53:25,318 --> 00:53:26,876
Thanks for the pill, Doc.

516
00:53:31,424 --> 00:53:34,723
Oh, by the way, Doc,

517
00:53:36,696 --> 00:53:39,529
I didn't find the autopsy report on Frankie.

518
00:53:40,300 --> 00:53:42,268
Have it sent over to my office
in the morning, will you?

519
00:53:42,335 --> 00:53:44,633
I'll need it
if the newspapers start screaming.

520
00:53:46,072 --> 00:53:48,506
You can send an aspirin along with it.

521
00:54:14,067 --> 00:54:17,230
- You murdered him.
- Shut up, you fool.

522
00:54:17,304 --> 00:54:19,534
I've got to get back
to my apartment right away.

523
00:54:19,606 --> 00:54:21,540
I'm a cinch to be
number two on Portugal's list

524
00:54:21,608 --> 00:54:23,473
when your place turns up empty.

525
00:54:23,543 --> 00:54:25,340
He can't pin a thing on me.

526
00:54:25,412 --> 00:54:27,107
Jo Jo doesn't play that way.

527
00:54:27,180 --> 00:54:28,875
If he's after you, he must know something.

528
00:54:28,949 --> 00:54:30,314
We've got to find out how much.

529
00:54:30,383 --> 00:54:32,908
- What then?
- We may have to run for it.

530
00:54:33,553 --> 00:54:35,350
How? The roads will all be locked tight.

531
00:54:35,422 --> 00:54:38,550
We can use Craig's car.
It's got doctor's plates.

532
00:54:38,625 --> 00:54:40,149
You'll have to drive.

533
00:54:44,931 --> 00:54:46,330
Get out.

534
00:54:47,600 --> 00:54:48,862
Both of you.

535
00:54:50,537 --> 00:54:51,868
Get out.

536
00:54:51,938 --> 00:54:53,166
Are you crazy?

537
00:54:53,239 --> 00:54:55,799
Portugal's men are
combing the city for Vincent.

538
00:54:55,875 --> 00:54:59,276
I don't care. I'm through.

539
00:54:59,346 --> 00:55:02,474
- You're nothing but...
- You'd better care and you're not through.

540
00:55:02,549 --> 00:55:05,882
You're in the middle. Deep.
Over your head.

541
00:55:05,952 --> 00:55:07,044
No matter what you do now,

542
00:55:07,120 --> 00:55:09,520
you're still part
of everything that's happened.

543
00:55:09,589 --> 00:55:11,989
You're part of the grab
for Frankie's money,

544
00:55:12,058 --> 00:55:14,993
you're part of the murder
that Portugal talked about tonight,

545
00:55:15,061 --> 00:55:19,020
even the manhunt for Vince,
you're part of that, too.

546
00:55:19,099 --> 00:55:22,660
You're as guilty as we are
and you might as well face it.

547
00:55:23,103 --> 00:55:25,037
- No, no.
- Yes.

548
00:55:25,105 --> 00:55:26,697
Ask Portugal.

549
00:55:26,773 --> 00:55:30,140
Ask him tomorrow when he finally gets
tired of waiting for an autopsy report

550
00:55:30,210 --> 00:55:33,646
that never arrives,
because there never was an autopsy.

551
00:56:13,620 --> 00:56:16,214
Vince, get the other half of the map.

552
00:56:16,823 --> 00:56:20,315
I'll phone you from my place
as soon as I know what's what.

553
00:56:47,520 --> 00:56:49,044
All alone?

554
00:56:49,122 --> 00:56:51,090
How did you get in here?

555
00:56:53,126 --> 00:56:55,822
Makes two angles I misfigured tonight.

556
00:56:57,897 --> 00:56:59,694
Must be the overtime.

557
00:56:59,766 --> 00:57:01,324
How did you get in here?

558
00:57:01,401 --> 00:57:03,562
Oh, getting in was easy.

559
00:57:03,636 --> 00:57:05,501
I'm a little worried about getting out.

560
00:57:05,572 --> 00:57:07,301
Georgia, what do you mean
by letting him in?

561
00:57:07,373 --> 00:57:09,136
He made me, Miss Margot. He made me.

562
00:57:09,209 --> 00:57:12,576
- Said if I didn't, he'd put me in jail.
- It's all right, Georgia. Go to bed.

563
00:57:15,215 --> 00:57:18,116
- Cup of coffee?
- Brave man.

564
00:57:18,184 --> 00:57:20,152
Good coffee. Georgia made it.

565
00:57:20,920 --> 00:57:22,615
What do you want?

566
00:57:22,689 --> 00:57:24,589
Picked up a couple
of knife-happy lads tonight.

567
00:57:24,657 --> 00:57:27,626
They were out playing games,
but they did a sloppy job.

568
00:57:27,694 --> 00:57:30,424
One of the guys they stuck
lived long enough to talk.

569
00:57:30,497 --> 00:57:31,794
Yes?

570
00:57:31,865 --> 00:57:35,460
One of the people he talked about
was your little playmate, Vincent.

571
00:57:35,535 --> 00:57:38,663
You mean you came here
looking for Jimmy?

572
00:57:38,738 --> 00:57:39,932
How disappointing.

573
00:57:40,006 --> 00:57:42,873
I thought you came because you
couldn't stay away from me any longer.

574
00:57:42,942 --> 00:57:45,172
Don't let that face of yours
go to your head.

575
00:57:45,245 --> 00:57:46,644
Or to yours?

576
00:57:48,648 --> 00:57:50,343
Wouldn't matter if it did.

577
00:57:50,950 --> 00:57:53,145
People who use pretty faces
like you use yours

578
00:57:53,219 --> 00:57:55,312
don't live very long, anyway.

579
00:57:55,388 --> 00:57:58,152
How do you think
I should use my face, Jo Jo?

580
00:57:58,224 --> 00:58:01,682
- You're rolling your own dice, kid.
- Maybe.

581
00:58:01,761 --> 00:58:03,695
I'd like to roll them for both of us.

582
00:58:03,763 --> 00:58:05,697
The way you did for Frankie Olins?

583
00:58:05,765 --> 00:58:07,733
He ran his own life and I ran mine.

584
00:58:07,800 --> 00:58:10,098
We had the same ideas. Just add it up.

585
00:58:10,170 --> 00:58:11,501
It's simple arithmetic.

586
00:58:11,571 --> 00:58:13,562
Didn't add up so good for Frankie.

587
00:58:13,640 --> 00:58:16,074
Why not?
He had what he wanted, didn't he?

588
00:58:16,142 --> 00:58:17,632
He spent more money in five years

589
00:58:17,710 --> 00:58:19,735
than you'll make if you live to be 500.

590
00:58:19,812 --> 00:58:23,145
- That's simple arithmetic, too.
- Yeah.

591
00:58:23,216 --> 00:58:24,740
Maybe I'll live.

592
00:58:24,817 --> 00:58:27,809
Maybe you won't,
if Jim Vincent sees you first.

593
00:58:30,590 --> 00:58:33,218
Want some more coffee before you go?

594
00:58:33,293 --> 00:58:35,318
Oh, no thanks. Save it.

595
00:58:35,395 --> 00:58:38,193
You may wake up someday
with an awful headache.

596
00:59:53,072 --> 00:59:54,869
- Hello?
<i>- Vince?</i>

597
00:59:54,941 --> 00:59:56,340
Yeah, this is Vince.

598
00:59:56,409 --> 00:59:59,572
Portugal's got you cold.
We'll have to run for it.

599
00:59:59,646 --> 01:00:03,673
I'll meet you at the corner of 16th
and Cherokee in 15 minutes, right?

600
01:00:03,750 --> 01:00:05,615
<i>How is he?</i>

601
01:00:05,685 --> 01:00:07,277
Oh, he's all right.

602
01:00:07,353 --> 01:00:08,581
<i>No trouble?</i>

603
01:00:09,789 --> 01:00:12,019
No, no trouble.

604
01:00:12,091 --> 01:00:13,615
We'll get it tonight.

605
01:00:13,693 --> 01:00:15,684
Yeah, we'll get the dough right away.

606
01:00:21,734 --> 01:00:25,534
Come on, Dr. Craig, get your hat and coat.

607
01:00:27,273 --> 01:00:29,764
Come on, come on.
We haven't got all night.

608
01:01:26,833 --> 01:01:30,064
Turn right, keep going straight
until you hit the State Highway.

609
01:01:43,916 --> 01:01:46,111
You can ride this road
right into Jordanville.

610
01:01:46,185 --> 01:01:49,279
- How far is it?
- About 150 or 160 miles.

611
01:01:49,355 --> 01:01:52,654
The dough is in a place just off
the highway about 12 miles past the town.

612
01:01:52,725 --> 01:01:53,851
Step on it.

613
01:02:17,450 --> 01:02:18,974
Police road block.

614
01:02:20,620 --> 01:02:21,882
Don't be a fool.

615
01:02:29,629 --> 01:02:31,563
All right, bud. Let's see your license.

616
01:02:38,938 --> 01:02:41,168
- Hey, what's the matter with him?
- He's sick.

617
01:02:41,240 --> 01:02:43,140
I'm the doctor at Watchaprague.

618
01:02:43,209 --> 01:02:45,439
Here's my Prison Bureau card.

619
01:02:46,312 --> 01:02:49,247
Oh, okay. Sorry to hold you up, Doc.
Go right ahead.

620
01:03:03,429 --> 01:03:04,953
Close.

621
01:03:05,031 --> 01:03:06,555
I need a drink after that.

622
01:03:06,632 --> 01:03:08,497
Yeah, me, too.

623
01:03:08,568 --> 01:03:10,695
Let's wait till we get through the town.

624
01:03:38,130 --> 01:03:41,258
Good evening.
Would you care to sit here, madam?

625
01:03:41,334 --> 01:03:42,665
No, there.

626
01:03:53,846 --> 01:03:55,905
Chili, hamburger, creamed chicken?

627
01:03:55,982 --> 01:03:58,246
- The creamed chicken...
- Get me a drink.

628
01:03:58,317 --> 01:04:00,148
Tea, coffee? The coffee's fresh.

629
01:04:00,219 --> 01:04:01,709
- Bourbon.
- Oh.

630
01:04:01,787 --> 01:04:04,085
I'll have some creamed chicken
and some coffee.

631
01:04:04,156 --> 01:04:06,249
And some Scotch first.

632
01:04:06,325 --> 01:04:07,986
The same.

633
01:04:23,209 --> 01:04:25,769
You handled that policeman
beautifully, Lloyd.

634
01:04:27,980 --> 01:04:29,072
Yeah.

635
01:04:30,650 --> 01:04:33,175
I had to learn sometime, didn't I?

636
01:04:36,589 --> 01:04:38,022
Didn't I?

637
01:04:41,961 --> 01:04:43,258
Yeah.

638
01:05:02,782 --> 01:05:04,113
Poor baby.

639
01:05:05,251 --> 01:05:06,741
Dead baby.

640
01:05:06,819 --> 01:05:08,480
You can't, Vince. We need him.

641
01:05:08,554 --> 01:05:10,613
What for? He's too drunk to drive.

642
01:05:11,357 --> 01:05:15,589
He's just dopey enough to start
feeling loud and sorry for himself.

643
01:05:15,661 --> 01:05:17,788
Maybe you need him.

644
01:05:17,863 --> 01:05:21,094
All I need is half of that 400,000.

645
01:05:21,167 --> 01:05:22,930
Half of that and me.

646
01:05:23,436 --> 01:05:27,338
- When do we...
- Oh, someplace between here and there.

647
01:05:28,074 --> 01:05:30,565
Come on.
I've got money singing in my brain.

648
01:05:30,643 --> 01:05:33,976
Wait a minute, wait a minute.
Let's check that map first.

649
01:05:43,589 --> 01:05:46,581
Ten feet from the eucalyptus tree,

650
01:05:46,659 --> 01:05:49,184
a quarter of a mile off the highway.

651
01:05:49,261 --> 01:05:51,320
Well, now, this is a cinch.

652
01:05:55,468 --> 01:05:56,901
Let's go.

653
01:06:09,281 --> 01:06:11,146
Try your luck on the punchboard, mister?

654
01:06:11,217 --> 01:06:12,514
Five cents a chance.

655
01:06:12,585 --> 01:06:15,213
Fellow in here yesterday
won pretty near $2.

656
01:06:15,921 --> 01:06:19,516
You know, dear,
we really can't afford it yet.

657
01:06:27,933 --> 01:06:29,366
You better get him.

658
01:06:29,435 --> 01:06:31,300
I'll meet you outside.

659
01:06:57,196 --> 01:06:58,390
You drive.

660
01:07:32,231 --> 01:07:35,359
- Flat, huh?
- Yeah, feels like it.

661
01:08:00,059 --> 01:08:02,926
Yeah, it's flat all right. Got a spare?

662
01:08:03,729 --> 01:08:06,493
Snap out of it, you. We gotta hurry.

663
01:08:06,565 --> 01:08:07,862
We're on a State Highway.

664
01:08:07,933 --> 01:08:10,128
He's in no condition.
You'll have to do it yourself.

665
01:08:10,202 --> 01:08:11,692
Take a look in the trunk.

666
01:08:20,012 --> 01:08:21,639
Yeah, we got one.

667
01:08:30,890 --> 01:08:32,755
All fixed. Got a puff?

668
01:08:36,796 --> 01:08:39,697
Ready to roll in a minute.
Just gotta let her down.

669
01:10:15,561 --> 01:10:17,586
I'd like to kill you.

670
01:11:30,869 --> 01:11:32,769
We're here! We're here!

671
01:11:32,838 --> 01:11:34,396
Don't you understand?

672
01:11:34,473 --> 01:11:37,169
Come on. Bring something to dig with.

673
01:11:51,223 --> 01:11:52,747
Lloyd, hurry!

674
01:12:01,633 --> 01:12:04,693
The eucalyptus trees.
Where's the hatchet mark?

675
01:12:09,942 --> 01:12:12,570
One, two, three,

676
01:12:12,644 --> 01:12:14,544
four, five,

677
01:12:14,613 --> 01:12:18,515
six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

678
01:12:20,352 --> 01:12:23,116
One, two, three,

679
01:12:23,188 --> 01:12:25,019
four, five.

680
01:12:30,062 --> 01:12:33,361
Lloyd, where are you, you fool?

681
01:12:33,432 --> 01:12:35,297
Lloyd, here, I found it!

682
01:12:35,367 --> 01:12:38,996
I found it, Lloyd! Come on!
Come and dig it!

683
01:12:39,571 --> 01:12:42,233
Come and dig for it! Dig!

684
01:12:47,646 --> 01:12:50,513
There it is, in the ground.

685
01:12:50,582 --> 01:12:52,880
It's right there beneath you, Lloyd.
In the ground.

686
01:12:52,951 --> 01:12:56,011
All our hopes, all our plans,

687
01:12:56,088 --> 01:12:58,283
they're all right there beneath you!

688
01:12:58,357 --> 01:13:00,257
Quickly, Lloyd, quickly.

689
01:13:00,325 --> 01:13:05,126
Dig for it! Deeper! Faster! Quickly, Lloyd!

690
01:13:05,197 --> 01:13:08,132
They killed for it! They all killed for it!

691
01:13:08,200 --> 01:13:10,930
Frankie, Vincent, I killed for it!

692
01:13:11,003 --> 01:13:14,530
And you, you too, you killed for it!

693
01:13:23,882 --> 01:13:26,407
Get off! Get off it!

694
01:13:26,485 --> 01:13:29,352
It's mine! It's all mine now!

695
01:13:30,556 --> 01:13:32,319
It's mine, I found it!

696
01:13:34,193 --> 01:13:35,888
It's mine!

697
01:13:45,604 --> 01:13:47,071
Mine.

698
01:13:47,606 --> 01:13:49,506
It's all mine now.

699
01:14:07,192 --> 01:14:09,990
Jo Jo, please,

700
01:14:10,062 --> 01:14:12,394
just this once,

701
01:14:12,464 --> 01:14:14,694
come down to my level.

702
01:14:41,293 --> 01:14:42,954
Simple arithmetic.

703
01:14:45,097 --> 01:14:46,758
That's all it was.

704
01:15:16,862 --> 01:15:19,353
"To you who double-crossed me,

705
01:15:20,632 --> 01:15:23,032
"I leave this dollar for your trouble.

706
01:15:24,069 --> 01:15:28,472
"The rest of the dough
I leave to the worms."

707
